{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","data":{"alias":"deadsmooth-provincial-shrew","description":"## Context\nThe 2026-07-14 \"calibration\" analysis (session log to be linked) found plan-review iteration excess is driven by: (1) a ~50-67% per-round BLOCK rate since calibration 2 (commit 96f5f374a, 2026-07-08), with 87% of blocking findings NEW each round; (2) one-defect-to-N-criterion blocking fan-out (up to 10 blocking findings per round from one defect, ticket a879); (3) the convergence rising floor never engaging (287/382 post-flip reviews ineligible, dominant cause: eligibility requires a prior CERTIFIED signature, which BLOCK loops never mint; 0 novelty drops ever recorded); (4) coaching notes + criteria-guide deep-links attach only to ADVISORY findings, never to the blocking findings agents must remediate; (5) plan authors are never routed to docs/plan-review-criteria-guide.md, so first drafts predictably fail the LLM tier; (6) the T5c security overlay contributes a large advisory wall (288 findings/7d, 0 blocks) including out-of-scope findings. The operator approved this non-Q2 remediation set for immediate implementation on 2026-07-14; the Q2 items (plan-v2 threshold replay + ac_unverifiable floor sub-grade) are explicitly OUT of this epic pending operator approval.\n\n## Success Criteria\n- The six child tickets below are closed with their changes landed on main through Gerrit (LLM-Review +1 AND Verified +1 per change).\n- Work is sequenced to avoid textual conflict with epic/audit-enrichment (ba33 / courtly-linear-iguana), which rewrites src/rebar/llm/plan_review/attest.py: the floor-eligibility story starts only after that epic's plan-review commits land on main.\n- No behavioral weakening of the gate: blocking findings still block; dedup groups findings, it does not drop them; coaching remains move-registry-constrained (the reviewer never writes plan text).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] All child tickets of this epic are closed.\n- [ ] Every child's change landed on main via Gerrit with both gate votes at +1 (visible in the change's vote history at rebar.solutions.navateam.com).\n- [ ] `make lint && make typecheck && make test` pass on main after the final child lands.","id":"d195-aeb8-2400-484b","parent_id":"","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"epic","title":"Plan-review cycle-reduction: approved 2026-07-14 calibration follow-up (non-Q2 set)"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1784085061903790001,"uuid":"f04accbb-dacd-43e9-bc1c-b51ae7a13d82"}